# Rocketship Overview

- **What Rocketship is**
  - Astro-focused component library designed to be highly themeable and CSS-first.
  - Lives in this pnpm monorepo alongside the Payload/Next backend and Astro frontend.
  - Long-term: full component suite comparable to other major UI libraries, plus a Payload template / collection / component library and optional Figma kit.

- **Core principles**
  - Prefer **SCSS/CSS over JavaScript**; MVP must be complete with CSS-only components and themes before any JS-required components are added.
  - Components are styled via **CSS custom properties** (`--rs-*`) with sensible fallback values.
  - Use **BEM with `rs` prefix** for all blocks (e.g. `.rs-button`, `.rs-button__icon`, `.rs-button--primary`).
  - **Design tokens** for colors, type, spacing, and component scales live in **`packages/base/src/styles/variables.scss`** on `:root` as `--rs-*` (no class selectors there). **Container-query widths** are Sass-only **`$rs-cq-sm` / `$rs-cq-md` / `$rs-cq-lg`** in `packages/base/src/styles/mixins/container-query.scss` so `@container` conditions get real lengths. Use `@include container-query-up($rs-cq-sm)` (etc.) in component or mixin SCSS; map size modifiers to the right `--rs-*` tokens inside those blocks.

- **Monorepo / packaging strategy**
  - Base package (e.g. `@rocketship/base`) exports primitives, design tokens, default theme, and core components.
  - Add-on packages (forms, layout, ecommerce, etc.) extend the system without breaking the base.
  - All packages are intended to be consumable via npm; internal apps (Astro frontend, Storybook) depend on them via workspace references.

- **Theming model**
  - Default theme = “rocketship / space-station” aesthetic, implemented as fallback values for `--rs-*`.
  - Eight planet themes shipped as separate packages of **CSS variable overrides only** (no components).
  - Light/dark variants per theme follow user preference; theming is purely CSS-based.

- **Docs and tooling**
  - `_planning/rocketship-plan.md` is the source of truth for project vision, decisions, and roadmap.
  - `_planning/tasks.md` holds the task list and acceptance criteria used by background agents.
  - **Storybook** runs inside the Astro frontend app (`apps/frontend`) via `@storybook-astro/framework` (Storybook 10). Stories render real Astro components from `@rocketship/base`. Run with `pnpm run dev:storybook` from the repo root. Stories use library components from `@rocketship/base` only. When storybook-astro’s one-component-per-story limit requires showing multiple components in one story, **Storybook-only wrapper components** (e.g. ButtonVariants, ButtonSizes) may be added under `apps/frontend/src/stories/components/`; they must only compose `@rocketship/base` components. Do not add Storybook wrapper components to the base package — the base package is for the published library only.
  - **No custom styles in stories:** Do not add `<style>` blocks, scoped component CSS, or story-only classes used purely for decoration in `apps/frontend/src/stories/**` or Storybook-only Astro wrappers. If something needs a visual treatment for real content, implement it in `@rocketship/base` (component or typography SCSS) so stories reflect what consumers get.

